# IC3Net_Belief_KL — Detailed Repository Summary

## What Is This?

A **PyTorch implementation of IC3Net** (*Individualized Controlled Continuous Communication Net*) from the ICLR 2019 paper [*"Learning when to Communicate at Scale in Multiagent Cooperative and Competitive Tasks"*](https://arxiv.org/abs/1812.09755). The repo name suffix `_Belief_KL` suggests it is a fork intended for extensions involving **belief modeling** and/or **KL-divergence**-based communication regularization, though those extensions have not yet been added to the codebase.

---

## High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["main.py<br/>(entry point, argparse, training loop)"] --> B["data.py<br/>(env factory)"]
    A --> C["CommNetMLP / RNN / MLP<br/>(policy networks)"]
    A --> D["Trainer<br/>(episode rollout + policy-gradient)"]
    A --> E["MultiProcessTrainer<br/>(parallel rollout workers)"]
    B --> F["GymWrapper<br/>(env_wrappers.py)"]
    F --> G["ic3net-envs<br/>(Predator-Prey, Traffic Junction)"]
    F --> H["gym-starcraft<br/>(StarCraft micro-management)"]
    D --> C
    E --> D
```

---

## Supported Communication Baselines

| Flag(s) | Model | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `--ic3net` | **IC3Net** | CommNet + learned **hard attention** gating (binary talk/silent) + individual rewards |
| `--commnet` | **CommNet** | Continuous communication, mean-pooled messages |
| `--mean_ratio 0` | **IRIC** | Individual-Reward IC (no cooperative mean blending) |
| *(none of above)* | **IC** | Independent Controller, no communication |
| `--random` | **Random** | Random policy baseline |

