## File-by-File Breakdown

### Core Training Pipeline

#### [main.py](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/main.py) — Entry Point (296 lines)
- Defines **all CLI arguments** (~110 flags): env name, number of agents, hidden size, learning rate, discount factor, communication settings, etc.
- Selects the policy network ([CommNetMLP](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/comm.py#8-254), [RNN](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/models.py#59-97), [MLP](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/models.py#8-35), or [Random](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/models.py#37-57)).
- Sets up [Trainer](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/trainer.py#14-263) or [MultiProcessTrainer](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/multi_processing.py#41-105) depending on `--nprocesses`.
- Runs the main **epoch loop**: calls [train_batch()](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/trainer.py#245-257), logs rewards/losses/success to a [log](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/utils.py#37-41) dict, optionally plots via **Visdom**.
- Handles save/load of model checkpoints (`.pt` files).

#### [trainer.py](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/trainer.py) — RL Training Logic (263 lines)
- **[Trainer](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/trainer.py#14-263) class** with:
  - **[get_episode(epoch)](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/trainer.py#26-127)** — Rolls out a single episode: resets env, iterates up to `max_steps`, queries the policy net at each step, records `Transition` tuples [(state, action, action_out, value, masks, next_state, reward, misc)](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/models.py#8-35).
  - **[compute_grad(batch)](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/trainer.py#128-226)** — Computes REINFORCE-style **policy gradient**:
    - Calculates **cooperative returns** (global mean reward) and **non-cooperative returns** (individual reward), blended by `--mean_ratio`.
    - Advantage = returns − value baseline.
    - Policy loss = −advantage × log π(a|s).
    - Value loss = MSE between predicted values and returns.
    - Entropy regularization (coefficient `--entr`).
  - **[run_batch(epoch)](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/trainer.py#227-243)** — Collects episodes until `batch_size` transitions are accumulated.
  - **[train_batch(epoch)](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/trainer.py#245-257)** — Single-process training: run batch → zero grad → compute grad → normalize by num_steps → optimizer step (RMSprop, α=0.97).

#### [multi_processing.py](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/multi_processing.py) — Parallel Workers (105 lines)
- **[MultiProcessWorker](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/multi_processing.py#6-39)** — A `torch.multiprocessing.Process` that owns its own [Trainer](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/trainer.py#14-263) replica, receives tasks via `mp.Pipe` ([run_batch](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/trainer.py#227-243), `send_grads`, [quit](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/multi_processing.py#56-59)).
- **[MultiProcessTrainer](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/multi_processing.py#41-105)** — Spawns `nprocesses − 1` workers; coordinates parallel episode collection, aggregates gradients, then calls `optimizer.step()` on the main process.

