### Neural Network Models

#### [models.py](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/models.py) — Simple Baselines (98 lines)
| Class | Description |
|---|---|
| [MLP](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/models.py#8-35) | 2-layer feedforward: `Linear(obs→hid)` → Tanh → residual `Linear(hid→hid)` + skip → action heads + value head. Supports continuous (Gaussian) and discrete actions. |
| [Random](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/models.py#37-57) | Outputs random log-softmax actions and random values. |
| [RNN](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/models.py#59-97) | Extends [MLP](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/models.py#8-35) by replacing the second linear layer with an **LSTMCell** (or plain RNN). Maintains hidden state across timesteps. |

#### [comm.py](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/comm.py) — CommNet / IC3Net (255 lines)
The **[CommNetMLP](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/comm.py#8-254)** class — the main contribution of the paper:

1. **State Encoder**: maps observation → hidden representation via a linear layer.
2. **Communication Loop** (runs `comm_passes` times):
   - Each agent's hidden state is broadcast to all other agents.
   - A **self-mask** prevents an agent from receiving its own message.
   - An **alive mask** zeros out dead agents.
   - If `--hard_attn` (IC3Net mode): a **gating action** (0 or 1) per agent controls whether it sends a message.
   - Messages are summed (or averaged if `--comm_mode avg`) and passed through a learned linear transform `C_modules[i]`.
   - The transformed communication is added to the encoded input (**skip connection**), then fed into `f_module` (LSTM cell or linear) to produce the next hidden state.
3. **Output**: action log-probabilities (discrete) or Gaussian params (continuous), plus a value head.

