### Environment Layer

#### [data.py](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/data.py) — Environment Factory (37 lines)
Creates and initializes environments by name (`levers`, `number_pairs`, `predator_prey`, `traffic_junction`, `starcraft`), wraps them in [GymWrapper](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/env_wrappers.py#7-108).

#### [env_wrappers.py](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/env_wrappers.py) — Gym Wrapper (108 lines)
[GymWrapper](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/env_wrappers.py#7-108) normalizes the interface for multi-agent envs:
- Exposes [observation_dim](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/env_wrappers.py#14-31), [num_actions](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/env_wrappers.py#32-40), [dim_actions](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/env_wrappers.py#41-51) properties.
- [reset(epoch)](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/env_wrappers.py#56-65) / [step(action)](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/env_wrappers.py#73-81) — handles both Discrete and MultiDiscrete action spaces.
- [_flatten_obs()](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/env_wrappers.py#88-101) — flattens per-agent observations into a [(1, N, obs_dim)](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/models.py#8-35) tensor.

#### [ic3net-envs/](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/ic3net-envs/) — Custom Gym Environments
An installable Python package (`python setup.py develop`) containing:
- **[predator_prey_env.py](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/ic3net-envs/ic3net_envs/predator_prey_env.py)** (~12 KB) — Grid-world where `N` predators must capture prey. Configurable grid size (`--dim`), agent vision (`--vision`), and difficulty.
- **[traffic_junction_env.py](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/ic3net-envs/ic3net_envs/traffic_junction_env.py)** (~22 KB) — Agents are cars navigating an intersection; must avoid collisions. Supports easy/medium/hard layouts with curriculum learning (`--add_rate_min/max`, `--curr_start/end`).
- **[traffic_helper.py](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/ic3net-envs/ic3net_envs/traffic_helper.py)** (~7 KB) — Route computation helpers for traffic junction.

#### [gym-starcraft/](file:///Users/Teoman/Desktop/Classes/NU/Spring26/RL/project/IC3Net_Belief_KL/gym-starcraft/) — StarCraft Micromanagement
Optional Gym wrapper around TorchCraft for explore and combat tasks.

